    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted given the Medium model influence and Medium decision consequence classification, and single-condition testing is standard practice for ASTM F1717 regulatory submissions. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended use. Note: the bench-test dataset (dataVintage 2025-09-30) and material property dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-15) predate the model revision of 2026-01-15; re-validation against the revised model build is planned for Q2 2026 and will be documented in a subsequent COU update.",
